# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: UnionKingdom | Scene: UnionKingdom7
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "Preparing for the feast, Sarah had done her best to appear every bit the ruler she was."
    new "Preparing for the feast, Sarah had done her best to appear every bit the ruler she was."

    old "Perhaps there was some vanity to it, but Sarah equally knew that men had a habit of treating her better when she looked her best."
    new "Perhaps there was some vanity to it, but Sarah equally knew that men had a habit of treating her better when she looked her best."

    old "Two of the other rulers of the Union Kingdom were men. If she could procure even the smallest advantage, it would be worth it."
    new "Two of the other rulers of the Union Kingdom were men. If she could procure even the smallest advantage, it would be worth it."

    old "When she arrived at the hall, her entrance was announced."
    new "When she arrived at the hall, her entrance was announced."

    old "All the nobles turned and looked at her."
    new "All the nobles turned and looked at her."

    old "Most likely many had heard of her, but few had seen her before."
    new "Most likely many had heard of her, but few had seen her before."

    old "The young ruler that had brought her nation to prosperity. Won a war over the savages. Brought low those who rose in rebellion."
    new "The young ruler that had brought her nation to prosperity. Won a war over the savages. Brought low those who rose in rebellion."

    old "She had a fair share of credit, given her young age."
    new "She had a fair share of credit, given her young age."

    old "And nobles were notorious gossips that lived for a good story or an interesting character."
    new "And nobles were notorious gossips that lived for a good story or an interesting character."

    old "One of the higher servants guided her towards her seat and Sarah sat down."
    new "One of the higher servants guided her towards her seat and Sarah sat down."

    old "Next to her, Queen Maeiv sat smiling."
    new "Next to her, Queen Maeiv sat smiling."

    old "Clever, Sarah thought."
    new "Clever, Sarah thought."

    old "She'd be close to her for most of the night. Whatever she hoped to discuss with anyone, Queen Maeiv would effortlessly listen in."
    new "She'd be close to her for most of the night. Whatever she hoped to discuss with anyone, Queen Maeiv would effortlessly listen in."

    old "The room looks stunning."
    new "The room looks stunning."

    old "Maeiv shrugged."
    new "Maeiv shrugged."

    old "The head-of-ceremony has been working in the castle for nearly eighty-years now."
    new "The head-of-ceremony has been working in the castle for nearly eighty-years now."

    old "Likely no man in all the Union that can do better than him."
    new "Likely no man in all the Union that can do better than him."

    old "Sarah saw an old man, near to death, balancing back and forth on his feet, shouting at some passing servants."
    new "Sarah saw an old man, near to death, balancing back and forth on his feet, shouting at some passing servants."

    old "Perhaps he should retire."
    new "Perhaps he should retire."

    old "Maeiv laughed."
    new "Maeiv laughed."

    old "Oh, I've suggested as much. Even told him he could have a royal pension."
    new "Oh, I've suggested as much. Even told him he could have a royal pension."

    old "But the man is inexhaustible. Lives for this."
    new "But the man is inexhaustible. Lives for this."

    old "He jokes that he'd likely die the day that he stops working, and I suspect it is only partially a joke."
    new "He jokes that he'd likely die the day that he stops working, and I suspect it is only partially a joke."

    old "She leaned back in her chair."
    new "She leaned back in her chair."

    old "No, he means to die in the harness. There is a beauty in that, I suppose. To know for certain your own role to play in life."
    new "No, he means to die in the harness. There is a beauty in that, I suppose. To know for certain your own role to play in life."

    old "Yes, it is admirable. There are servants in Rosanna as well, that are older than myself, some even older than my father."
    new "Yes, it is admirable. There are servants in Rosanna as well, that are older than myself, some even older than my father."

    old "The things they must have seen over the years..."
    new "The things they must have seen over the years..."

    old "Maeiv placed one hand on her wrist."
    new "Maeiv placed one hand on her wrist."

    old "Your dear father. I had the pleasure of meeting him once, many years ago now."
    new "Your dear father. I had the pleasure of meeting him once, many years ago now."

    old "Hearing someone else speak about her father put Sarah on edge."
    new "Hearing someone else speak about her father put Sarah on edge."

    old "You did?"
    new "You did?"

    old "Maeiv nodded."
    new "Maeiv nodded."

    old "He attended court, back when I was still...well, not Queen."
    new "He attended court, back when I was still...well, not Queen."

    old "She smiled as she said it."
    new "She smiled as she said it."

    old "I remember even as a little girl seeing him and thinking, that is what a king should look like."
    new "I remember even as a little girl seeing him and thinking, that is what a king should look like."

    old "Yes, that much is very true."
    new "Yes, that much is very true."

    old "Our king back then was...well, a bit less of your father, more Duke Antonio."
    new "Our king back then was...well, a bit less of your father, more Duke Antonio."

    old "Maeiv laughed at her own joke."
    new "Maeiv laughed at her own joke."

    old "Sarah smiled, wanting neither to cause offense by not laughing, nor cause offense to another by laughing too much."
    new "Sarah smiled, wanting neither to cause offense by not laughing, nor cause offense to another by laughing too much."

    old "Every move or gesture seemed to carry hidden meaning here."
    new "Every move or gesture seemed to carry hidden meaning here."

    old "It was not long after when the first course was begun to be put out."
    new "It was not long after when the first course was begun to be put out."

    old "A near army of servants rushed into the room, carrying an almost equally impossible amount of food."
    new "A near army of servants rushed into the room, carrying an almost equally impossible amount of food."

    old "Mountains of food and drinks in equal measure."
    new "Mountains of food and drinks in equal measure."

    old "Sarah had often felt embarrassed at the wealth on display at her own feasts."
    new "Sarah had often felt embarrassed at the wealth on display at her own feasts."

    old "This was something different altogether."
    new "This was something different altogether."

    old "The opulence on display here, the excess, it balanced somewhere between the absurd and the horrifying."
    new "The opulence on display here, the excess, it balanced somewhere between the absurd and the horrifying."

    old "As Sarah joined in, she could barely help contain her shame."
    new "As Sarah joined in, she could barely help contain her shame."

    old "All along the table she saw the Normandi nobles, appearing far less troubled by the affair."
    new "All along the table she saw the Normandi nobles, appearing far less troubled by the affair."

    old "A greedy noble, round and fat as a pig, shoved a sausage into his mouth."
    new "A greedy noble, round and fat as a pig, shoved a sausage into his mouth."

    old "As his stained teeth chewed through half of it, it broke apart."
    new "As his stained teeth chewed through half of it, it broke apart."

    old "Half the sausage dissapeared into his greedy mouth, grease splattering across his face, caught in his beard."
    new "Half the sausage dissapeared into his greedy mouth, grease splattering across his face, caught in his beard."

    old "The other half fell onto the ground."
    new "The other half fell onto the ground."

    old "The waste that the man displayed was no exception, if anything, it appeared the rule."
    new "The waste that the man displayed was no exception, if anything, it appeared the rule."

    old "A servant quickly rushed up, sweeping away the remants of food that fell on the floor."
    new "A servant quickly rushed up, sweeping away the remants of food that fell on the floor."

    old "The nobleman appeared more piglet than man."
    new "The nobleman appeared more piglet than man."

    old "Sarah shuddered."
    new "Sarah shuddered."

    old "On the other side, she more nobles, men and ladies alike, gorging themselves on the food."
    new "On the other side, she more nobles, men and ladies alike, gorging themselves on the food."

    old "The table stretched for most of the length of the room."
    new "The table stretched for most of the length of the room."

    old "Wine poured down throats so quickly, she wondered if anyone even tasted anything at all."
    new "Wine poured down throats so quickly, she wondered if anyone even tasted anything at all."

    old "No plate was left empty for long. No cup ever dried up."
    new "No plate was left empty for long. No cup ever dried up."

    old "There was always a servant, quick to serve."
    new "There was always a servant, quick to serve."

    old "The more the evening carried on, the more the thing appeared like a nightmare."
    new "The more the evening carried on, the more the thing appeared like a nightmare."

    old "Sarah looked from the corner of her eyes at her host."
    new "Sarah looked from the corner of her eyes at her host."

    old "Queen Maeiv sat back in her chair, comfortable, laughing at something one of the nobles nearby said."
    new "Queen Maeiv sat back in her chair, comfortable, laughing at something one of the nobles nearby said."

    old "Her plate of food, by contrast, was only lightly touched. Her cup only refilled once."
    new "Her plate of food, by contrast, was only lightly touched. Her cup only refilled once."

    old "Are all celebrations like this?"
    new "Are all celebrations like this?"

    old "Excuse me dear?"
    new "Excuse me dear?"

    old "I mean, are all feasts in Normandi so...grand?"
    new "I mean, are all feasts in Normandi so...grand?"

    old "Maeiv chuckled."
    new "Maeiv chuckled."

    old "The people of Delphine are used to enjoying themselves."
    new "The people of Delphine are used to enjoying themselves."

    old "You don't think this is...excessive?"
    new "You don't think this is...excessive?"

    old "All the people in this room make up everyone that matters in Normandi."
    new "All the people in this room make up everyone that matters in Normandi."

    old "She gestured at one of the nobles."
    new "She gestured at one of the nobles."

    old "He controls most of the lumber camps up north."
    new "He controls most of the lumber camps up north."

    old "She gestured to the next."
    new "She gestured to the next."

    old "She inherited several gem mines in the interior."
    new "She inherited several gem mines in the interior."

    old "All put together, these are the people that make the country run."
    new "All put together, these are the people that make the country run."

    old "And do you see what they're up to?"
    new "And do you see what they're up to?"

    old "Sarah looked around, all she could see was the carnage that passed for a feast."
    new "Sarah looked around, all she could see was the carnage that passed for a feast."

    old "They're happy."
    new "They're happy."

    old "Happy little piggies eating at the trough."
    new "Happy little piggies eating at the trough."

    old "And happy piggies don't have a reason to complain or rebel."
    new "And happy piggies don't have a reason to complain or rebel."

    old "She looked directly at Sarah."
    new "She looked directly at Sarah."

    old "I imagined you of all people should understand the risk of unhappy noble families."
    new "I imagined you of all people should understand the risk of unhappy noble families."

    old "Sarah gritted her teeth. There was some truth to the accusation."
    new "Sarah gritted her teeth. There was some truth to the accusation."

    old "Perhaps so, but still...to have so much when there is so much poverty, isn't that-"
    new "Perhaps so, but still...to have so much when there is so much poverty, isn't that-"

    old "Ooh dear, please."
    new "Ooh dear, please."

    old "Things like these keep the nobles fat and happy."
    new "Things like these keep the nobles fat and happy."

    old "You think this is vile?"
    new "You think this is vile?"

    old "Maeiv leaned in closer and lowered her voice."
    new "Maeiv leaned in closer and lowered her voice."

    old "When you broke the armies of that fool Marion, who do you think made up the bulk of those armies?"
    new "When you broke the armies of that fool Marion, who do you think made up the bulk of those armies?"

    old "So I indulge these people a bit. Let them live large. In turn they keep the peace."
    new "So I indulge these people a bit. Let them live large. In turn they keep the peace."

    old "Keep stability."
    new "Keep stability."

    old "I watched this country nearly ripped apart when these fools couldn't figure out who should sit on the throne."
    new "I watched this country nearly ripped apart when these fools couldn't figure out who should sit on the throne."

    old "And you know what?"
    new "And you know what?"

    old "Sarah looked at Maeiv."
    new "Sarah looked at Maeiv."

    old "The truth is these idiots would do it all over again."
    new "The truth is these idiots would do it all over again."

    old "All they want is an excuse. Some insult, some perceived slight, and they'd gather their swords again."
    new "All they want is an excuse. Some insult, some perceived slight, and they'd gather their swords again."

    old "And as most of the other countries in the Union prospered, we stagnated."
    new "And as most of the other countries in the Union prospered, we stagnated."

    old "They think because we have so much, we can never lose it. They don't see how everyone else is catching up to us already."
    new "They think because we have so much, we can never lose it. They don't see how everyone else is catching up to us already."

    old "She didn't quite agree, but she understood where all this excess was coming from."
    new "She didn't quite agree, but she understood where all this excess was coming from."

    old "It was more than simple greed."
    new "It was more than simple greed."

    old "Now forgive me, there are some particular fat piggies that require even more gladhanding."
    new "Now forgive me, there are some particular fat piggies that require even more gladhanding."

    old "Sarah watched as Queen Maeiv stood up and walked up towards a group of nobles."
    new "Sarah watched as Queen Maeiv stood up and walked up towards a group of nobles."

    old "Her entire demeanour changed, full of energy and smiling faces."
    new "Her entire demeanour changed, full of energy and smiling faces."

    old "Sarah sat by herself for a moment, taking in the room."
    new "Sarah sat by herself for a moment, taking in the room."

    old "She tried counting the many nobles, but quickly realized whatever their number was, it far exceeded her ability to count."
    new "She tried counting the many nobles, but quickly realized whatever their number was, it far exceeded her ability to count."

    old "Normandi was rich, she always knew that, but she never knew it was quite this wealthy."
    new "Normandi was rich, she always knew that, but she never knew it was quite this wealthy."

    old "Suddenly, she saw a man move up from the corner of her eyes."
    new "Suddenly, she saw a man move up from the corner of her eyes."

    old "The big-bellied jovial man plomped down in the seat next to her."
    new "The big-bellied jovial man plomped down in the seat next to her."

    old "What a pleasure to finally meet with you in person."
    new "What a pleasure to finally meet with you in person."

    old "Duke Antonio, it could have been nobody else."
    new "Duke Antonio, it could have been nobody else."

    old "Duke Antonio, a pleasure to meet you as well in person. How did you know who I was?"
    new "Duke Antonio, a pleasure to meet you as well in person. How did you know who I was?"

    old "Oh, you're a striking image for your late father."
    new "Oh, you're a striking image for your late father."

    old "More feminine, I suppose, but the traits are definitely there in your face."
    new "More feminine, I suppose, but the traits are definitely there in your face."

    old "Sarah kept forcing her smile, not sure what to make of his comment."
    new "Sarah kept forcing her smile, not sure what to make of his comment."

    old "I didn't know you had met my father."
    new "I didn't know you had met my father."

    old "He nodded."
    new "He nodded."

    old "Many years ago now. I was still only a simple council member, not yet voted in."
    new "Many years ago now. I was still only a simple council member, not yet voted in."

    old "Medini, the country that Antonio sat at the head of, was different from the other Union Kingdoms."
    new "Medini, the country that Antonio sat at the head of, was different from the other Union Kingdoms."

    old "Each of the nine great cities offered up one council member, and collectively they ruled the country."
    new "Each of the nine great cities offered up one council member, and collectively they ruled the country."

    old "The head of the council was granted the title of Duke, but only reserved that seat through holding onto the required votes."
    new "The head of the council was granted the title of Duke, but only reserved that seat through holding onto the required votes."

    old "At a moment's notice, the other council members could withdraw their support and bring down a Duke."
    new "At a moment's notice, the other council members could withdraw their support and bring down a Duke."

    old "Duke Antonio in that regard was the latest in a long line of Dukes."
    new "Duke Antonio in that regard was the latest in a long line of Dukes."

    old "Medini liked to abuse their own system."
    new "Medini liked to abuse their own system."

    old "Often a Duke would make a promise to one of the other countries, but when the time came to collect, the old Duke would be gone and a new Duke would be seated."
    new "Often a Duke would make a promise to one of the other countries, but when the time came to collect, the old Duke would be gone and a new Duke would be seated."

    old "And the new Duke would argue that surely he could not be held responsible for the promises of another."
    new "And the new Duke would argue that surely he could not be held responsible for the promises of another."

    old "Over the centuries, this had won them a reputation for dishonesty. They themselves called it cleverness."
    new "Over the centuries, this had won them a reputation for dishonesty. They themselves called it cleverness."

    old "I wish I had known that you met with my father."
    new "I wish I had known that you met with my father."

    old "He waved his hand."
    new "He waved his hand."

    old "Please, I don't suppose I made much of an impression on your father."
    new "Please, I don't suppose I made much of an impression on your father."

    old "I think he thought most of us were pretentious merchants."
    new "I think he thought most of us were pretentious merchants."

    old "No, my father deeply respected the Medini people, I don't think he would ever-"
    new "No, my father deeply respected the Medini people, I don't think he would ever-"

    old "Duke Antonio threw up a hand."
    new "Duke Antonio threw up a hand."

    old "No need for flattery."
    new "No need for flattery."

    old "The accusation would have been true. Most of us are just overly serious merchants."
    new "The accusation would have been true. Most of us are just overly serious merchants."

    old "His laugh bouldered through the room."
    new "His laugh bouldered through the room."

    old "Well, regardless, I am glad to finally meet you in person."
    new "Well, regardless, I am glad to finally meet you in person."

    old "Duke Antonio nodded."
    new "Duke Antonio nodded."

    old "We have communicated through letters plenty, and I must say, I always look forward to each piece of state correspondence."
    new "We have communicated through letters plenty, and I must say, I always look forward to each piece of state correspondence."

    old "But I must admit, it always feels so dry."
    new "But I must admit, it always feels so dry."

    old "To meet and speak in person, so much better to form a relationship."
    new "To meet and speak in person, so much better to form a relationship."

    old "All the best trade deals are struck over a good meal and drink."
    new "All the best trade deals are struck over a good meal and drink."

    old "Sarah watched as he grabbed the pitcher of wine and refilled his cup, then motioned for hers."
    new "Sarah watched as he grabbed the pitcher of wine and refilled his cup, then motioned for hers."

    old "Sarah threw up one hand."
    new "Sarah threw up one hand."

    old "No, thank you. I think I have had more than my share already. I can feel myself dizzy."
    new "No, thank you. I think I have had more than my share already. I can feel myself dizzy."

    old "Duke Antonio leaned back in his chair, nursing his cup of wine."
    new "Duke Antonio leaned back in his chair, nursing his cup of wine."

    old "Ah, yes. I must admit, even I struggle to keep up with these Normandi folk, and we in Medini know how to throw a good party."
    new "Ah, yes. I must admit, even I struggle to keep up with these Normandi folk, and we in Medini know how to throw a good party."

    old "Sarah observed the man. Given his proportions, she didn't doubt it."
    new "Sarah observed the man. Given his proportions, she didn't doubt it."

    old "Duke Antonio, if I may ask you..."
    new "Duke Antonio, if I may ask you..."

    old "Of course, ask me anything. I am at your disposal."
    new "Of course, ask me anything. I am at your disposal."

    old "Have you any notion of what this Union Council is concerning?"
    new "Have you any notion of what this Union Council is concerning?"

    old "She saw his face turn to a frown."
    new "She saw his face turn to a frown."

    old "Business talk, and so soon."
    new "Business talk, and so soon."

    old "But unfortunately, I must dissapoint you. I know little more than you do, it seems."
    new "But unfortunately, I must dissapoint you. I know little more than you do, it seems."

    old "And still you came."
    new "And still you came."

    old "I suppose I did. Same reason as yourself, perhaps. A fascination with what this Silent Queen is up to."
    new "I suppose I did. Same reason as yourself, perhaps. A fascination with what this Silent Queen is up to."

    old "Sarah leaned back in her chair."
    new "Sarah leaned back in her chair."

    old "She was frustrated to learn nothing new, but happy to realize she probably wasn't the only one in the dark."
    new "She was frustrated to learn nothing new, but happy to realize she probably wasn't the only one in the dark."

    old "Sarah saw Duke Antonio's eyes drift away across the room, his attention caught by something."
    new "Sarah saw Duke Antonio's eyes drift away across the room, his attention caught by something."

    old "When she looked, realized it was a someone."
    new "When she looked, realized it was a someone."

    old "Please forgive me, Sarah. It appears someone needs my assistance."
    new "Please forgive me, Sarah. It appears someone needs my assistance."

    old "A raven-haired servant girl, perhaps only just twenty, did her best to carry a plate stacked with food."
    new "A raven-haired servant girl, perhaps only just twenty, did her best to carry a plate stacked with food."

    old "Sarah watched as Duke Antonion descended on her with all smiles and offers of help."
    new "Sarah watched as Duke Antonion descended on her with all smiles and offers of help."

    old "The foolish girl took it, even thanking him for the assistance in carrying the tray."
    new "The foolish girl took it, even thanking him for the assistance in carrying the tray."

    old "She'd be in his bed before long."
    new "She'd be in his bed before long."

    old "Sarah shook her head. It was remarkable how some men, regardless of status, could all be reduced to a handful of base instincts."
    new "Sarah shook her head. It was remarkable how some men, regardless of status, could all be reduced to a handful of base instincts."

    old "She saw a man lean across the now empty chair."
    new "She saw a man lean across the now empty chair."

    old "Repulsive, really."
    new "Repulsive, really."

    old "Sarah looked over and saw that it was Marshal Edmond."
    new "Sarah looked over and saw that it was Marshal Edmond."

    old "His gaunt face and lean appearance hinted at a life quite different from Duke Antonio's."
    new "His gaunt face and lean appearance hinted at a life quite different from Duke Antonio's."

    old "More self denial than debauchery."
    new "More self denial than debauchery."

    old "What was that, sir Edmond?"
    new "What was that, sir Edmond?"

    old "He gestured at Antonio with the servant girl. The Duke now had an arm wrapped around her waist."
    new "He gestured at Antonio with the servant girl. The Duke now had an arm wrapped around her waist."

    old "I said it's repulsive."
    new "I said it's repulsive."

    old "A man of his age with a girl like that."
    new "A man of his age with a girl like that."

    old "Sarah did her best to remain neutral."
    new "Sarah did her best to remain neutral."

    old "She didn't disagree, but she also didn't want to speak ill of the Duke."
    new "She didn't disagree, but she also didn't want to speak ill of the Duke."

    old "Sarah couldn't be sure whose support she might need during the Union Council. Best not to alienate anyone too soon."
    new "Sarah couldn't be sure whose support she might need during the Union Council. Best not to alienate anyone too soon."

    old "Well, he enjoys life and all that it offers, I suppose."
    new "Well, he enjoys life and all that it offers, I suppose."

    old "She saw Edmond frown."
    new "She saw Edmond frown."

    old "And the girl?"
    new "And the girl?"

    old "Sarah was startled by the question."
    new "Sarah was startled by the question."

    old "What of her?"
    new "What of her?"

    old "The servant girl. You think she enjoys life and all that it offers?"
    new "The servant girl. You think she enjoys life and all that it offers?"

    old "You think when she's beneath the bloated bastard tonight, the bed creaking as he's crushing her, you think she'll enjoy life?"
    new "You think when she's beneath the bloated bastard tonight, the bed creaking as he's crushing her, you think she'll enjoy life?"

    old "Sarah was startled by his directness."
    new "Sarah was startled by his directness."

    old "Of course not."
    new "Of course not."

    old "The only reason a girl like that gives a man like him a moment of attention is because she knows who he is."
    new "The only reason a girl like that gives a man like him a moment of attention is because she knows who he is."

    old "And she knows that even a fraction of his wealth is more than she can earn in a lifetime."
    new "And she knows that even a fraction of his wealth is more than she can earn in a lifetime."

    old "Edmond fell down into the chair."
    new "Edmond fell down into the chair."

    old "Funny, isn't that?"
    new "Funny, isn't that?"

    old "An amount of money that he probably wouldn't even miss, is enough to buy a girl's life, just like that."
    new "An amount of money that he probably wouldn't even miss, is enough to buy a girl's life, just like that."

    old "I don't think he's looking to buy her life."
    new "I don't think he's looking to buy her life."

    old "Edmon suddenly laughed."
    new "Edmon suddenly laughed."

    old "Ah, so you do have claws."
    new "Ah, so you do have claws."

    old "Sarah looked at him."
    new "Sarah looked at him."

    old "I am not unaware of the matters that you hint at."
    new "I am not unaware of the matters that you hint at."

    old "But the world won't change here tonight."
    new "But the world won't change here tonight."

    old "Edmond shrugged."
    new "Edmond shrugged."

    old "It might not tonight, but perhaps this week."
    new "It might not tonight, but perhaps this week."

    old "Sarah leaned in closer."
    new "Sarah leaned in closer."

    old "You know anything about the Union Council?"
    new "You know anything about the Union Council?"

    old "Edmond nodded."
    new "Edmond nodded."

    old "Not too much, but I've heard some whispers here and there."
    new "Not too much, but I've heard some whispers here and there."

    old "Such as..."
    new "Such as..."

    old "You would ask me to give away my secrets?"
    new "You would ask me to give away my secrets?"

    old "You don't strike me as a man that enjoys keeping secrets and playing in shadows."
    new "You don't strike me as a man that enjoys keeping secrets and playing in shadows."

    old "Edmond laughed."
    new "Edmond laughed."

    old "You don't really know me all that well, girl."
    new "You don't really know me all that well, girl."

    old "Sarah sat back in her chair."
    new "Sarah sat back in her chair."

    old "I am not a girl, I am your peer, as I am that of Queen Maeiv and Duke Antonio."
    new "I am not a girl, I am your peer, as I am that of Queen Maeiv and Duke Antonio."

    old "And I imagined we might speak more plainly with one another."
    new "And I imagined we might speak more plainly with one another."

    old "Edmond raised an eyebrow."
    new "Edmond raised an eyebrow."

    old "And why would that be?"
    new "And why would that be?"

    old "Because we share a similar concern, or so I have been told. A consideration for the plight of those who have less."
